  <h1> Why UX design is a highly underrated job:</h1>
    <p> As a <strong>UX designer </strong> you get to solve real-world problems, as well as the tiny,
      day-to-day, seemingly insignificant problems (that actually add up to a lot!).
      It’s all in the name, <em>User Experience design </em>—the user and their needs are at the
      forefront of the design process, whether it’s an app, a website, financial services,
      or the layout of a shop.
    </p>

    <h3> Reasons why UX designers are in demnad: </h3>
    <ul>
      <li>A Chance to be both Creative and Logical </li>
      <li>An easy switch from any career </li>
      <li>No need to master any tools </li>
      <li>Opportunities for skills development, growth and specialization </li>



